Health &amp; Human Services Dept, RI

************************************************************************


Record request #26-137 has been closed. The closure reason supplied was:

Please see attached, in response to your records request. 



The records deemed public in the possession of the Rhode Island Department of Health (RIDOH) are attached hereto. We note that some of the records you requested are deemed not to be public pursuant to (i) R.I. Gen. Laws § 38-2.2(4)(A)(1)(a), which protects information subject to attorney-client privilege from disclosure, and § 38-2-2(4)(K) which protects preliminary drafts, notes, impressions, memoranda, working papers, and work products. 

&nbsp;

R.I. Gen. Laws § 38-2-8 requires we provide you notice of your right to appeal this response to the Director of Health, Attention Legal Services, Three Capitol Hill, Providence, RI 02908, file a complaint with the Department of the Attorney General, 150 South Main Street, Providence, Rhode Island, 02903, or file a complaint with the Rhode Island Superior Court of the county where the relevant records are maintained.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Further information concerning the Access to Public Records Act is available through the Attorney General’s website at www.riag.ri.gov&nbsp;&nbsp;








